text: Crimmitschau () is a town in the rural district of Zwickau in the Free State of Saxony, Germany. The first documentation of Crimmitschau is from 1212. ==Population== {| class="prettytable" Year Population 1834 3,767 1875 17,649 1880 18,925 1890 19,300 1933 27,938 1939 27,247 1946 30,504 1950 34,541 1960 31,279 1981 26,229 1984 25,086 ==References== ==Other websites== Category:Zwickau Rural District
